Confirming that our elections are conducted with integrity which is what this current process is working to prove- should be commended not condemned.
For the sake of our Republic we must allow the process to run its course and once the litigation is settled we can talk about a transition if necessary. ...
There are real legal questions surrounding if voting deadline can be extended in violation of state law and whether poll watchers were denied appropriate access to observe the voting process. ...
There are multiple cries of- “there’s no evidence of fraud” but legal proceedings and evidentiary matters are determined by the courts not media outlets and political pundits.  ...
I don’t recall the mainstream media criticizing Mr. Gore.    The paint is not dry from this election. There are states who have yet to complete the counting process. ...

President Trump has every right to pursue the legal challenges afforded to him as a candidate.  In 2000 Vice President Al Gore refused to concede the election for more than 30 days while he pursued legal action attempting to change the results in Florida.  I don’t recall...
